New Records: Harry Kane is expected to start on what would be his 100th senior appearance for England, becoming just the 10th man to reach a century of England caps.

England could match an all-time national team unbeaten record if they claim at least a point over Finland, equaling their record for the most games against a single country without ever suffering defeat.
Key Match Events: Harry Kane scored two goals at the 57th and 76th minutes to secure a 2-0 victory for England.
Schuller received a yellow card at the 66th minute.
Pre-Game Insights: England were aiming to equal their all-time national team unbeaten record against Finland.
Lee Carsley was looking to avoid consecutive home defeats, a feat not seen since Roy Hodgson's tenure in 2013.
Harry Kane was anticipated to make his 100th senior appearance for England.
Post-Match Reflections: Lee Carsley aimed to join an exclusive club of England managers who have won both of their opening matches in charge.
Miscellaneous Highlights: England have not been beaten in any of their first 11 meetings with Finland, winning nine and drawing two.
This was the first meeting between England and Finland since March 2001.
